French machinery maker &lt;Poclain>, 40 pctowned by &lt;Tenneco Inc>, said it will raise its capital to 791mln francs from 91 mln by a 100 for 13 rights offering toshareholders priced at par of 10 francs a share.    The offer, between March 25 and April 13, is the secondstage of a capital restructuring plan announced in Decemberunder which Tenneco will become Poclain's majority shareholder.    In the first stage Poclain reduced its capital to 91 mlnfrom 455 mln by reducing the nominal value of its shares to 10francs from 50.    Poclain traded Friday on the Paris Bourse at 38.20 francs. REUTER&#3;